After adjusting for age, sex, refraction, history of smoking, treatment of I131, generalized estimation equations were used to analyze the correlations between the SNR values of icVEPs under the 8%, 16%, and 32% DOM and clinical factors in non-DON and DON groups (Table 2). The SNR values under 8%, 16% and 32% DOM were significantly strongly negatively correlated with BCVA (p = 0.038, r = − 0.6; p < 0.001, r = − 0.7; p < 0.001, r = − 0.9), papilledema (Y/N) (p = 0.006, r = − 0.4; p = 0.002, r = − 0.6; p = 0.010, r = − 0.8) and DON (Y/N) (p < 0.001, r = − 0.5; p < 0.001, r = − 0.6; p < 0.001, r = − 0.7). The SNR values under 8%, 16% and 32% DOM were significantly weakly positively correlated with MD(dB) (p = 0.033, r = 0;
